\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 9. TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Problem: The HUD loads, but Drive/Steer says "Disconnected".
\f2\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f3\i \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Cause:
\f2\i0  The Python backend cannot read the USB ports, or the hardware disconnected.\
\ls9\ilvl0
\f3\i \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Solution:
\f2\i0  Open Settings > Microcontrollers > Click "FORCE RE-SCAN USBs". If this fails, open the Web Terminal and run dmesg | grep tty to see if the USB cable vibrated loose.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Problem: Steering is twitching or acting erratic.
\f2\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0
\f3\i \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Cause:
\f2\i0  The ESP8266 is browning out due to the servo drawing too much power, or the auto-center failsafe is fighting your commands.\
\ls10\ilvl0
\f3\i \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Solution:
\f2\i0  Go to Settings > Microcontrollers and set "Centering Time" to 0.0s to test if the failsafe is triggering prematurely. Ensure the servo is powered by a dedicated BEC, not the ESP8266 5V pin.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Problem: Drone instantly drops to 0% battery when throttling up.
\f2\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0
\f3\i \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Cause:
\f2\i0  Voltage sag is dipping below the limit, and your Battery Settings are incorrect.\
\ls11\ilvl0
\f3\i \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Solution:
\f2\i0  Go to Settings > Battery. Ensure your parallel packs and mAh are correctly entered. The system calculates sag via (Amps / Pack Count) * 0.015. If the total mAh is set too low, the math assumes massive failure.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Problem: Camera feed is a black screen, but HUD loads.
\f2\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0
\f3\i \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Cause:
\f2\i0  FFmpeg crashed or the Logitech camera disconnected.\
\ls12\ilvl0
\f3\i \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Solution:
\f2\i0  Open the Web Terminal and run sudo systemctl restart drone-cam. Refresh the browser after 5 seconds.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Problem: Reverse doesn't work immediately after driving forward.
\f2\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0
\f3\i \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Cause:
\f2\i0  This is a safety feature to prevent gear shredding.\
\ls13\ilvl0
\f3\i \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Solution:
\f2\i0  The system enforces a default 3.0-second lockout between direction changes. To disable this (Not Recommended), go to Settings > Microcontrollers > Failsafe Seconds, and set it to 0.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa321\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs48 \cf0 \outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u55358 \u56800 
\f4\b  PART 1: DRIVE CONTROLLER (ARDUINO UNO)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f5\b0\fs24 \cf0 The Arduino Uno is strictly responsible for handling the electronic speed controller (ESC), monitoring power consumption (Voltage/Amperage), driving the physical TM1637 LCD display, and managing hardware-level failsafes (like preventing the gears from stripping when shifting from forward to reverse).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs28 \cf0 1. Hardware & Pin Definitions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls14\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Pins 2 & 3:
\f5\b0  Connected to the TM1637 4-digit display (Clock and Data).\
\ls14\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Analog A0:
\f5\b0  Connected to a Current (Amperage) sensor.\
\ls14\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Analog A1:
\f5\b0  Connected to a Voltage sensor via a voltage divider.\
\ls14\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Pin 9:
\f5\b0  Generates the PWM signal for the motor's Electronic Speed Controller (ESC).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs28 \cf0 2. Core Measurement Functions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0
\f6\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 getVolts()
\f5\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f7 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What it does:
\f5\b0  Reads the raw analog value from pin A1 30 times and averages it to smooth out electrical noise.\
\ls15\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f7 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 How it works:
\f5\b0  It multiplies the raw value by the sensor's distance multiplier (
\f8\fs26 distV
\f5\fs24 ) and the hardware voltage divider ratio (
\f8\fs26 vDividerRatio
\f5\fs24 ). It then adds the software calibration offset (
\f8\fs26 v_offset
\f5\fs24 ) to ensure hyper-accurate readings.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0
\f6\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 getAmps()
\f5\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f7 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What it does:
\f5\b0  Calculates the live current draw of the motors.\
\ls15\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f7 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 How it works:
\f5\b0  It takes 100 rapid samples from pin A0. It compares this against the 
\f8\fs26 zeroPoint
\f5\fs24  (calibrated at boot). It calculates the difference, applies the sensor's sensitivity multiplier, and finally passes the result through an aggressive 
\f4\b Low-Pass Filter
\f5\b0  (
\f8\fs26 (currentAmps * 0.1) + (filteredAmps * 0.9)
\f5\fs24 ). This prevents the amperage spikes from looking jittery on the HUD.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0
\f6\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 getBatteryPercentage()
\f5\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f7 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What it does:
\f5\b0  Calculates a highly accurate, sag-corrected battery percentage that doesn't "bounce" around when driving.\
\ls15\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f7 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 How it works (The Ratchet Algorithm):
\f5\b0  1. It calculates 
\f9\i Voltage Sag
\f5\i0  by looking at the current Amps drawn divided by the number of parallel batteries. 2. It applies a heavy smoothing filter to the voltage to ignore sudden throttle punches. 3. It maps the voltage to a 0\'96100 scale depending on if you selected LiPo or NiMH in the settings. 4. 
\f4\b The Ratchet:
\f5\b0  It uses a variable called 
\f8\fs26 current_pct
\f5\fs24 . The code states: 
\f8\fs26 if (calc_pct < current_pct) current_pct = calc_pct;
\f5\fs24 . This means the battery percentage on the HUD can 
\f9\i only go down, never up
\f5\i0 . This prevents the battery from dropping to 40% under hard acceleration and bouncing back to 80% when you stop.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs28 \cf0 3. Display & Animation Functions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
